P.M. BRIEFING; 
BRITISH FIRM TO BUY L.A. AD AGENCY 
WPP Group PLC, the British-based advertising and marketing services giant, said 
today it has agreed to buy Seiniger Advertising Inc., a Los Angeles-based 
agency that specializes in marketing movies. 
The deal calls for an initial payment of $10 million in cash and stock and 
additional payments of up to another $20 million in cash and stock based on the 
agency's financial performance over the next four years. 
Seiniger was launched in 1974 and has marketed more than 650 movies, including 
campaigns for the movies "Bull Durham," "Indiana Jones and the Last Crusade," 
"Jaws" and "The Untouchables." 
